      "id": "RQ-0005",
      "status": "done",
      "title": "Harden webhook runtime lifecycle and config validation",
      "description": "The audit found a reliability gap in Ralph's webhook runtime: one dispatcher startup failure disables delivery for the rest of the run, dispatcher teardown does not coordinate worker/scheduler shutdown, and webhook numeric settings are documented with bounds that are not enforced consistently at config-validation time. This task should make webhook startup failures recoverable, shutdown deterministic, and config validation explicit so operators get fast, actionable failures instead of silent runtime drift or permanent disablement.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "audit",
        "webhook",
        "reliability",
        "config",
        "runtime"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/runtime/state.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/runtime/dispatcher.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/runtime/",
        "crates/ralph/src/contracts/config/webhook.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/config/validation/",
        "crates/ralph/src/webhook/tests/",
        "cargo test -p ralph-agent-loop webhook"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "User request: \"use the comprehensive codebase audit skill and build tasks stemming from your findings\"",
        "crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/runtime/state.rs:72-105 permanently short-circuits dispatcher creation once `disabled_reason` is set after a startup failure.",
        "crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/runtime/dispatcher.rs:48-121 spawns worker and scheduler threads during startup, while lines 124-131 only log during `Drop` and do not coordinate teardown.",
        "crates/ralph/src/contracts/config/webhook.rs:119-140 documents numeric bounds for timeout, retries, backoff, queue capacity, and parallel multiplier, but lines 218-237 only validate enablement and URL safety.",
        "The operability audit also flagged inconsistent runtime handling of webhook settings and late shutdown/noise risk in the retry scheduler path."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Trace the webhook runtime lifecycle from config resolution through dispatcher build, rebuild, delivery, retry scheduling, and shutdown.",
        "Replace the current permanent-disable-once behavior with a bounded retry or circuit-breaker approach that preserves diagnostics without killing delivery for the full process lifetime.",
        "Add explicit shutdown signaling and thread join coordination for dispatcher worker and retry-scheduler threads so rebuilds and exits are deterministic.",
        "Centralize webhook numeric validation at config-load or run-entry time and remove inconsistent mixtures of documented bounds, silent clamps, and unchecked runtime adoption.",
        "Add focused runtime and config-validation tests that cover startup failure recovery, teardown behavior, unsafe/out-of-range webhook settings, and redacted operator-facing errors.",
        "Run the webhook-focused Rust tests and any broader local gate needed to prove the hardened runtime behaves correctly."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "use the comprehensive codebase audit skill and build tasks stemming from your findings",
