      "id": "RQ-0018",
      "status": "done",
      "title": "Enforce `machine_error` version checks before retry/recovery classification",
      "description": "Principles violated: E (make bugs hard to write), F (fail fast), J (consistency/integrity). RalphMac defines `RalphMachineContract.errorVersion` but `MachineErrorDocument.decode(from:)` bypasses contract validation and accepts any version value. Retry and recovery paths then trust that decoded payload as authoritative. Why it matters: incompatible `machine_error` payloads can be misclassified as valid structured errors, masking contract drift and producing incorrect retry/recovery behavior. Minimal fix: move machine-error decoding behind contract validation and reject unsupported versions with explicit recovery errors. Acceptance criteria: malformed/unknown machine-error versions no longer classify as valid machine errors; supported version behavior remains unchanged.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "ralphmac",
        "machine-contract",
        "reliability"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/ConfigModels.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/MachineContract.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/RetryHelper.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/RalphCLIRecoveryClassifier.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/RalphCLIClient+Retry.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCoreTests/"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/MachineContract.swift:44 :: errorVersion constant :: defined but unused elsewhere",
        "path: apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/ConfigModels.swift:204-209 :: MachineErrorDocument.decode :: direct JSONDecoder decode with no version validation",
        "path: apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/RetryHelper.swift:96,215 :: defaultShouldRetry/isRetryableFailure :: trusts MachineErrorDocument.decode(stderr)",
        "path: apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/RalphCLIRecoveryClassifier.swift:48,129 :: classify :: trusts MachineErrorDocument.decode(description/stderr)",
        "workflow: rg -n \"RalphMachineContract\\.errorVersion\" apps/RalphMac/RalphCore --glob '*.swift' :: only declaration found, no enforcement call sites"
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Make `MachineErrorDocument` conform to the versioned-document contract and validate against `RalphMachineContract.errorVersion`.",
        "Refactor callers to use the contract-validated decode path instead of raw permissive decode.",
        "Ensure unsupported error-document versions return explicit version-mismatch classification rather than falling through as valid structured errors.",
        "Add regression tests for supported vs unsupported machine-error versions across retry and recovery classifiers.",
        "Verify by running `xcodebuild test -project apps/RalphMac/RalphMac.xcodeproj -scheme RalphCore -destination 'platform=macOS,arch=$(uname -m)' -only-testing:RalphCoreTests/RetryHelperTests -only-testing:RalphCoreTests/ErrorRecoveryCategoryTests`."
