      "id": "RQ-0017",
      "status": "done",
      "title": "Version-gate `machine system info` in RalphMac compatibility checks",
      "description": "Principles violated: E (make bugs hard to write), F (fail fast), J (consistency/integrity). `WorkspaceManager+Versioning.executeVersionCheck` decodes `MachineSystemInfoDocument` directly without validating the machine document version, even though Ralph’s machine contract is explicitly versioned. This allows incompatible payload shapes to flow into compatibility logic without a clear contract error. Why it matters: a future CLI/document version bump can cause false compatibility outcomes or ambiguous errors during app startup/version checks. Minimal fix: make `MachineSystemInfoDocument` conform to `VersionedMachineDocument`, add a `systemInfoVersion` constant in `RalphMachineContract`, and decode through `RalphMachineContract.decode(...)`. Acceptance criteria: mismatched system-info version produces `.versionMismatch` recovery messaging; matched version still validates normally.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "ralphmac",
        "machine-contract",
        "correctness"
      ],
      "scope": [
