        "crates/ralph/src/cli/machine/queue.rs",
        "docs/machine-contract.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: crates/ralph/src/cli/machine/common.rs:84-103 :: `build_queue_read_document` loads queue/done and computes runnability without queue validation.",
        "repro: temp queue with task missing `created_at`, run `/tmp/ralph-scan-target/debug/ralph queue validate` and `/tmp/ralph-scan-target/debug/ralph machine queue read` :: expected queue-read state to reflect invalid/stalled continuation :: actual validate exits 1 (`Missing created_at`) while machine queue read exits 0 and returns `next_runnable_task_id: RQ-0001`",
        "path: docs/machine-contract.md:206 :: `runnability.summary.blocking` is documented as queue/read source of truth for operator blocking state"
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Introduce shared validation-aware queue-read assembly so machine queue-read consumers cannot bypass structural validity checks.",
