      "id": "RQ-0045",
      "status": "done",
      "title": "Restore resolved queue and done paths in parallel-worker cleanup",
      "description": "Principles violated: J (consistency/integrity), C (DRY knowledge), H (operational hygiene). Parallel-worker post-run cleanup hardcodes `.ralph/queue.jsonc` and `.ralph/done.jsonc` instead of using the resolved queue and done paths that worker execution already honors. Why it matters: repos with custom `queue.file` or `queue.done_file` can leave their real bookkeeping files dirty after worker supervision, so custom queue/done artifacts can leak into worker commits or block finalization even though the default paths were restored. Minimal fix: drive cleanup and dirty-path detection from `resolved.queue_path` / `resolved.done_path` plus the workspace-mapped equivalents instead of hardcoded default filenames. Acceptance criteria: a regression with custom queue and done paths proves worker cleanup restores the real bookkeeping files and leaves no lingering bookkeeping dirtiness, and the targeted parallel supervision tests pass.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "parallel",
        "bookkeeping"
      ],
      "scope": [
