        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/supervision/parallel_worker/tests.rs:81-154 :: restore_bookkeeping_uses_workspace_paths_when_coordinator_paths_are_overridden only changes coordinator paths while the workspace restore still targets hardcoded .ralph/queue.jsonc and .ralph/done.jsonc",
        "workflow: cargo test -p ralph-agent-loop parallel :: current suite passes without a regression that exercises custom workspace bookkeeping paths during post-run supervision cleanup"
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Replace the hardcoded restore and bookkeeping-dirtiness path lists with resolved queue and done paths mapped into the worker workspace.",
        "Keep generated cache cleanup separate from resolved bookkeeping restoration so custom queue/done paths remain the single source of truth.",
        "Add a targeted supervision regression that uses custom queue and done paths and asserts the real bookkeeping files are restored cleanly.",
        "Verify by running `cargo test -p ralph-agent-loop parallel` and confirming custom queue/done supervision no longer leaves bookkeeping dirtiness behind."
