    {
      "id": "RQ-0056",
      "status": "done",
      "title": "Deeply investigate and fix parallel-mode queue/done sync for gitignored JSONC queues",
      "description": "Perform a thorough root-cause investigation and remediation for `ralph run loop --parallel 2` when a target repository keeps `.ralph/queue.jsonc` and `.ralph/done.jsonc` gitignored. Prior attempted fixes are not sufficient: after parallel workspace agents finish, commit, and push, the source/root repository's queue and done JSONC files can remain stale instead of reflecting completed worker bookkeeping. The outcome must be a durable, tested parallel-mode synchronization contract that updates coordinator-resolved queue/done paths for gitignored JSONC files without relying on git-tracked propagation.",
      "priority": "critical",
      "tags": [
        "parallel-mode",
        "queue-sync",
        "gitignored-files",
        "jsonc",
        "bug",
        "data-integrity",
        "undo",
        "atomic-writes"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "AGENTS.md",
        ".ralph/queue.jsonc",
        ".ralph/done.jsonc",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/orchestration/events.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/orchestration/loop_runtime.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/mod.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/common.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/tests/bookkeeping.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/integration/bookkeeping.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/integration/tests.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/worker.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/worker_process.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/queue/",
        "crates/ralph/src/fsutil/atomic.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/undo/",
        "crates/ralph/src/runutil/shell/",
        "crates/ralph/tests/run_parallel_test/",
        "crates/ralph/tests/parallel_done_json_safety_test/",
        "crates/ralph/tests/test_support*",
        "ralph run loop --parallel 2",
        "cargo test run_parallel",
        "make agent-ci"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "User report on 2026-04-27: in a repository where `.ralph/done.jsonc` and `.ralph/queue.jsonc` are gitignored, running `ralph run loop --parallel 2` can leave the source/root repo queue/done JSONC files stale after workspace agents finish, commit, and push.",
        "User report says prior attempted fixes were not sufficient, so this requires root-cause investigation, not another narrow copyback patch.",
        "Repository guidance says worker workspace setup mirrors repo-local `.ralph/` runtime files recursively except ephemeral `.ralph/{cache,workspaces,logs,lock}/`, and must seed queue/done from coordinator-resolved paths including `.jsonc` and custom paths so gitignored `.ralph` repos work in parallel mode.",
        "Repository guidance says parallel worker post-run bookkeeping restore must target workspace-local `.ralph/{queue.json,queue.jsonc,done.json,done.jsonc,cache/productivity.json}` and fail fast if bookkeeping paths remain dirty after restore.",
        "Because queue/done are gitignored, normal worker commit/push propagation cannot update the coordinator source files; the coordinator must explicitly merge worker terminal results into the current coordinator-resolved queue/done files.",
        "Code finding: `handle_finished_workers` treats a successful worker by fast-forwarding the coordinator branch and then calling `sync::sync_worker_bookkeeping_back_to_source(resolved, &workspace.path)` in `crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/orchestration/events.rs`; it currently has no task-level coordinator reconciliation step.",
        "Code finding: `sync_worker_bookkeeping_back_to_source` in `crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/mod.rs` delegates queue and done separately to `sync_worker_bookkeeping_file_back_to_source`; tracked paths return early and untracked/gitignored paths copy the entire worker file over the coordinator file with `common::sync_file_if_exists`.",
        "Code finding: `common::sync_file_if_exists` uses direct `fs::copy`; initial seeding may tolerate this, but coordinator source-of-truth queue/done writeback should use validated `queue::save_queue` / `fsutil::write_atomic` and undo snapshots.",
        "Code finding: worker integration rebuilds bookkeeping from `origin/<target>` only if the path exists in the remote ref; if the path is gitignored/untracked, `restore_bookkeeping_path_from_ref` logs that it is not tracked and leaves the worker local copy intact.",
        "Code finding: `archive_current_task` then archives only the current worker task against that worker-local snapshot and saves the worker-local queue/done. With two workers seeded from the same ignored queue, each worker can contain its own completion plus stale state for the sibling task.",
        "Likely causal chain: ignored queue/done cannot be refreshed from git, each worker reconciles against its initial snapshot, and coordinator success handling copies whole ignored files back to root. Multiple successful workers therefore produce last-writer-wins behavior that can resurrect tasks or drop sibling done entries.",
        "Coverage gap: existing tests cover single-worker ignored-bookkeeping copyback and tracked-path git authority, but not two concurrent ignored JSONC workers finishing from the same seed queue where both completions must be merged into coordinator root files.",
        "Coverage gap: `parallel_done_json_safety_test` checks parseability/conflict safety but should add semantic assertions that completed tasks are removed from root queue, root done contains each completed task exactly once, and no task ID exists in both queue and done.",
        "Design risk: ignored/untracked bookkeeping copyback performs raw whole-file replacement without queue validation, undo checkpoint creation, task-level reconciliation, or order-independence.",
